{
  "texts": [
    "The core of the algorithm lies in its high speed and sensitivity, making it excellent at handling large-scale protein sequence databases.",
    "DIAMOND rapidly retrieves and matches query sequences during the alignment phase by converting protein sequences from reference databases into a compressed index format.",
    "It also introduces the use of spacer seeds to improve performance in sequence comparison.",
    "DIAMOND is used in a wide range of applications, including genome annotation, metabolic pathway analysis, and microbial community analysis.",
    "Due to its high speed and efficiency, it has become an important tool in bioinformatics research and big data analysis."
  ]
}